@nickwallen Unfortunately, there's no any spec files in place to test it and it requires a lot of mocking in order to test this small "feature" because the component is already a huge "monolith". 
We're planning to cover the functionalities with the proper unit and integration tests. We already have an [ASF Jira ticket](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/METRON-1907) on this. I've linked the two together an set it as it incorporates with the aforementioned migrating ticket.
If you agreed, we could merge the two independently from each other.

@ottobackwards I addressed your feedback.  Ran it up again and re-tested just to be sure. 

```
[root@node1 0.7.0]# cat triage-test.stellar
t := THREAT_TRIAGE_INIT()
THREAT_TRIAGE_ADD(t, {"name":"rule1", "rule":"value>10", "score":10})
THREAT_TRIAGE_ADD(t, {"name":"rule2", "rule":"value>20", "score":"value*10"})
THREAT_TRIAGE_PRINT(t)
msg1 := "{ \"value\":22 }"
msg2 := "{ \"value\":44 }"
THREAT_TRIAGE_SCORE( msg1, t)
THREAT_TRIAGE_SCORE( msg2, t)
```
